\fs28 \cf0 2.1 Architecture Decisions to Avoid\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa319\partightenfactor0

\fs24 \cf0 Over-Engineering\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f2\b0\fs26 \cf0 \uc0\u10060 
\f4  DON'T:\
- Implement microservices architecture\
- Add message queues (Redis, RabbitMQ) unless absolutely necessary\
- Build custom authentication instead of using Supabase Auth\
- Create abstraction layers "for future flexibility"\
- Implement GraphQL (REST is sufficient for this scope)\
- Add caching layers prematurely (Vercel handles edge caching)\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa319\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs24 \cf0 Database Design\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f2\b0\fs26 \cf0 \uc0\u10060 
\f4  DON'T:\
- Create overly normalized schemas (some denormalization is fine)\
- Add audit/history tables for every entity (start simple)\
- Implement soft deletes on everything (only where business logic requires)\
- Build complex permission systems in the database\
- Store JSON blobs for structured data that should be relational\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa319\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs24 \cf0 State Management\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f2\b0\fs26 \cf0 \uc0\u10060 
\f4  DON'T:\
- Add Redux, MobX, or Zustand unless proven necessary\
- Implement complex client-side caching (use React Query/SWR if needed)\
- Build custom form state management (use react-hook-form)\
- Create global state for data that can be fetched on demand\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa280\partightenfactor0

